list_definition_mean.definition: to think deeply
ex_of_definition_list: He was meditating on his troubles.

list_definition_mean.definition: to spend short, regular periods in deep (especially religious) thought
ex_of_definition_list: He meditates twice a day.

list_definition_mean.definition: something by or through which an effect is produced
ex_of_definition_list: Air is the medium through which sound is carried.

list_definition_mean.definition: a means (especially radio, television and newspapers) by which news etc is made known
ex_of_definition_list: the news media.

list_definition_mean.definition: a person through whom spirits of dead people are said to speak
ex_of_definition_list: I know a medium who says she can communicate with Napoleon.

list_definition_mean.definition: middle or average in size, quality etc
ex_of_definition_list: Would you like the small, medium or large packet?

list_definition_mean.definition: to come face to face with (eg a person whom one knows), by chance
ex_of_definition_list: She met a man on the train.

list_definition_mean.definition: (sometimes, especially American, with with) to come together with (a person etc), by arrangement
ex_of_definition_list: The committee meets every Monday.

list_definition_mean.definition: to be introduced to (someone) for the first time
ex_of_definition_list: Come and meet my wife.

list_definition_mean.definition: to join
ex_of_definition_list: Where do the two roads meet?

list_definition_mean.definition: to be equal to or satisfy (eg a person’s needs, requirements etc)

list_definition_mean.definition: to come into the view, experience or presence of
ex_of_definition_list: A terrible sight met him / his eyes when he opened the door.

list_definition_mean.definition: to come to or be faced with
ex_of_definition_list: He met his death in a car accident.

list_definition_mean.definition: (with with) to experience or suffer; to receive a particular response
ex_of_definition_list: She met with an accident
The scheme met with their approval.

list_definition_mean.definition: to answer or oppose
ex_of_definition_list: We will meet force with greater force.

list_definition_mean.definition: a gathering, especially of sportsmen
ex_of_definition_list: The local athletics club are holding a meet this week.

list_definition_mean.definition: a very large stone that is part of a prehistoric monument

list_definition_mean.definition: a funnel-shaped device for speaking through, that causes sounds to be made louder and/or sent in a given direction
ex_of_definition_list: He shouted instructions to the crowd through a megaphone.

list_definition_mean.definition: a tune
ex_of_definition_list: He played Irish melodies on the harp.

list_definition_mean.definition: the principal part in a piece of harmonized music
ex_of_definition_list: The sopranos sang the melody, and the other voices added the harmony.

list_definition_mean.definition: its firm yellow or red flesh as food
ex_of_definition_list: We started the meal with melon
(also adjective) a melon seed.

list_definition_mean.definition: to (cause to) become soft or liquid, or to lose shape, usually by heating / being heated
ex_of_definition_list: The ice has melted
My heart melted when I saw how sorry he was.

list_definition_mean.definition: the state of being a member
ex_of_definition_list: membership of the Communist Party.

list_definition_mean.definition: a group of members
ex_of_definition_list: a professional society with a large membership.

list_definition_mean.definition: the amount of money paid to a society etc in order to become a member
ex_of_definition_list: The membership has increased to $5 this year.

list_definition_mean.definition: a person who belongs to a group, club, society, trade union etc
ex_of_definition_list: The association has three thousand members.

list_definition_mean.definition: a thin film or layer of tissue that covers or lines parts of the body, forms the outside of cells etc
ex_of_definition_list: There is a membrane located just inside the eggshell.

list_definition_mean.definition: something (eg a monument) that honours/honors or commemorates people or events of the past
ex_of_definition_list: a memorial to Sir Winston Churchill
a war memorial.

list_definition_mean.definition: the power to remember things
ex_of_definition_list: He has a good memory for details.

list_definition_mean.definition: the mind’s store of remembered things
ex_of_definition_list: Her memory is full of interesting stories.

list_definition_mean.definition: something remembered
ex_of_definition_list: memories of her childhood.

list_definition_mean.definition: the time as far back as can be remembered
ex_of_definition_list: the coldest winter in memory.

list_definition_mean.definition: a serious disease in which there is inflammation of the membranes round the brain or spinal cord
ex_of_definition_list: the symptoms of meningitis.

list_definition_mean.definition: clothing for men
ex_of_definition_list: Do you sell menswear?
(also adjective) the menswear department.

list_definition_mean.definition: (a level of) mental power
ex_of_definition_list: The team needs to develop a winning mentality.

list_definition_mean.definition: of the mind
ex_of_definition_list: mental illnesses/disorders.

list_definition_mean.definition: done or made by the mind
ex_of_definition_list: mental arithmetic
a mental picture.

list_definition_mean.definition: for those who are ill in mind
ex_of_definition_list: a mental hospital.

list_definition_mean.definition: suffering from an illness of the mind
ex_of_definition_list: a mental patient.

list_definition_mean.definition: a sharp-smelling substance got from peppermint oil used to help give relief from colds etc
ex_of_definition_list: If you have a cold put some menthol in boiling water and breathe in the steam
Some cigarettes contain menthol.

list_definition_mean.definition: to speak of or refer to
ex_of_definition_list: He mentioned the plan.

list_definition_mean.definition: to remark or say usually briefly or indirectly
ex_of_definition_list: She mentioned (that) she might be leaving.

list_definition_mean.definition: (often with of) a (usually brief) remark (about)
ex_of_definition_list: No mention was made of this matter.

list_definition_mean.definition: (a card with) a list of dishes that may be ordered at a meal
ex_of_definition_list: What’s on the menu today?

list_definition_mean.definition: a list of options on a computer screen, from which a user can choose
ex_of_definition_list: a drop-down menu.

list_definition_mean.definition: goods to be bought and sold
ex_of_definition_list: This store sells merchandise from all over the world.

list_definition_mean.definition: a trader, especially wholesale, in goods of a particular kind
ex_of_definition_list: a timber/tea/wine merchant.

list_definition_mean.definition: a joining together of business firms
ex_of_definition_list: There’s been a merger between two companies.

list_definition_mean.definition: to (cause to) combine or join
ex_of_definition_list: The sea and sky appear to merge at the horizon.

list_definition_mean.definition: (with into) to change gradually into something else
ex_of_definition_list: Summer slowly merged into autumn.

list_definition_mean.definition: (with into etc) to disappear into (eg a crowd, back-ground etc)
ex_of_definition_list: He merged into the crowd.

list_definition_mean.definition: (one of) the openings between the threads of a net
ex_of_definition_list: a net with (a) very fine (= small) mesh.

list_definition_mean.definition: a network
ex_of_definition_list: A fly was struggling in the meshes of the spider’s web.

list_definition_mean.definition: (of teeth on eg gear wheels) to become engaged with each other
ex_of_definition_list: The teeth on these two cogwheels mesh when they go round.

list_definition_mean.definition: a piece of information spoken or written, passed from one person to another
ex_of_definition_list: I have a message for you from Mr Johnston.

list_definition_mean.definition: the instruction or teaching of a moral story, religion, prophet etc
ex_of_definition_list: What message is this story trying to give us?

list_definition_mean.definition: a state of disorder or confusion; an untidy, dirty or unpleasant sight or muddle
ex_of_definition_list: This room is in a terrible mess!
She looked a mess
The spilt food made a mess on the carpet.

list_definition_mean.definition: (with with) to meddle, or to have something to do with
ex_of_definition_list: She’s always messing with the television set.

list_definition_mean.definition: all the chemical processes that occur within a living thing in order to maintain life, resulting in growth and the production of energy from food
ex_of_definition_list: Exercise speeds up the body’s metabolism.

list_definition_mean.definition: (of) any of a group of substances, usually shiny, that can conduct heat and electricity and can be hammered into shape, or drawn out in sheets, bars etc
ex_of_definition_list: Gold, silver and iron are all metals.

list_definition_mean.definition: (of) a combination of more than one of such substances
ex_of_definition_list: Brass is a metal made from copper and zinc.

list_definition_mean.definition: (a) marked change of form, appearance, character etc
ex_of_definition_list: a caterpillar’s metamorphosis into a butterfly.

list_definition_mean.definition: a form of expression (not using ’like’ or ’as’)in which a quality or characteristic is given to a person or thing by using a name, image, adjective etc normally used of something else which has similar qualities etc
ex_of_definition_list: ‘He’s a tiger when he’s angry’ is an example of (a) metaphor.

list_definition_mean.definition: a small meteor that has fallen to earth
ex_of_definition_list: meteorites burning up in the atmosphere.

list_definition_mean.definition: (also shooting star) a small mass or body travelling very quickly through space which appears very bright after entering the earth’s atmosphere
ex_of_definition_list: a meteor shower.

list_definition_mean.definition: an instrument for measuring, especially quantities of electricity, gas, water etc
ex_of_definition_list: a parking meter
If you want to know how much electricity you have used, you will have to look at the meter.

list_definition_mean.definition: to measure (especially electricity etc) by using a meter
ex_of_definition_list: This instrument meters rainfall.

list_definition_mean.definition: the methods and principles that you use to carry out a particular activity or when studying a particular subject
ex_of_definition_list: language teaching methodology.

list_definition_mean.definition: the way in which one does something
ex_of_definition_list: I don’t like his methods of training workers.

list_definition_mean.definition: an orderly or fixed series of actions for doing something
ex_of_definition_list: Follow the method set down in the instruction book.

list_definition_mean.definition: good sense and a definite plan
ex_of_definition_list: Her work seems to lack method.

list_definition_mean.definition: of the metre or metric system
ex_of_definition_list: Are these scales metric?

list_definition_mean.definition: a very tiny living thing invisible to the naked eye, especially a germ causing disease
ex_of_definition_list: a new understanding of how this microbe causes disease.

list_definition_mean.definition: the scientific study of microorganisms
ex_of_definition_list: She’s studying microbiology at the University of Nottingham.

list_definition_mean.definition: (also chip) computing a very small piece of silicon or another semiconductor that carries a series of electrical circuits and is used in computers and other machines
ex_of_definition_list: a silicon microchip.

list_definition_mean.definition: (abbreviation mikemaik) an electronic instrument for picking up sound waves to be broadcast, recorded or amplified as in radio, the telephone, a tape-recorder etc
ex_of_definition_list: Speak into the microphone.

list_definition_mean.definition: an instrument which makes very small objects able to be seen magnifying them greatly
ex_of_definition_list: Germs are very small, and can only be seen with the aid of a microscope.

list_definition_mean.definition: (also microwave oven) an oven that heats or cooks food very quickly using electromagnetic waves
ex_of_definition_list: I generally only use the microwave for cooking rice.

list_definition_mean.definition: to cook or heat something in a microwave
ex_of_definition_list: Microwave the ready meal for three minutes.

list_definition_mean.definition: the central point or part
ex_of_definition_list: the middle of a circle.

list_definition_mean.definition: the central area of the body; the waist
ex_of_definition_list: You’re getting rather fat round your middle.

list_definition_mean.definition: equally distant from both ends
ex_of_definition_list: the middle seat in a row.

list_definition_mean.definition: at, or in, the middle of
ex_of_definition_list: a midweek football match
in mid air
a mid-air collision between two aircraft.

list_definition_mean.definition: (an attack of) a type of very severe headache, often accompanied by vomiting and difficulty in seeing
ex_of_definition_list: She suffers from migraine.

list_definition_mean.definition: a very important event
ex_of_definition_list: The discovery of penicillin was a milestone in medical history.

list_definition_mean.definition: of soldiers or armed forces generally, or war
ex_of_definition_list: military supplies/discipline/power.

list_definition_mean.definition: a drink made by shaking up milk and a particular flavouring/flavoring
ex_of_definition_list: I’d like a chocolate/strawberry milkshake.

list_definition_mean.definition: containing milk
ex_of_definition_list: milky coffee.

list_definition_mean.definition: like milk in appearance
ex_of_definition_list: A milky substance.
